    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-21T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/6081: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-21T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 21, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3245. American Interests Germany. Department’s A–45, February 7. Swiss note May
                    15 states that according letter April 21 from Swiss Legation, Berlin, German
                    authorities appear recently to have taken up passports those internees not
                    considered Aryan. This does not involve withdrawal as such but a control measure
                    because passports are returned to bearers after verification their identity and
                    nationality. When interested persons unable furnish sufficient proof of
                    nationality it may be assumed they are transferred special Jewish camps.</p>
                <p>Thus far Swiss Legation, Berlin, has knowledge no case where American passport
                    not returned to bearer after control. Appears German authorities more
                    particularly interested in bearers Palestinian and certain Latin American
                    passports.</p>
                <p>Swiss promise such supplementary information as may be obtained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
